Create the Blazor WASM pages and components for a construction site inspection PWA app.

Working directory: /tmp/sv-d2dd13e687734e22a73607d363aa276a/SiteInspector.Client

The app uses these services (already being created separately):
- `IndexedDbService` - CRUD for sites, inspections, photos via IndexedDB
- `SyncService` - syncs pending inspections to server

Models (in SiteInspector.Shared.Models):
- `ConstructionSite` { Id, Name, Address, Notes, CreatedAt }
- `Inspection` { Id, SiteId, SiteName, InspectorName, InspectedAt, Notes, Status (enum: InProgress/Completed/NeedsFollowUp), ChecklistItems, Photos, SyncState (enum: Pending/Synced/Failed), LastSyncedAt }
- `ChecklistItem` { Id, Category, Description, Result (enum: NotChecked/Pass/Fail/NotApplicable), Notes, SortOrder }
- `PhotoRecord` { Id, FileName, Caption, TakenAt, FileSizeBytes }
- `ChecklistTemplates.GetSafetyChecklist()` returns a default list of ChecklistItem

The app has these pages. Create each one:

### 1. Pages/Home.razor - Dashboard
Route: "/"

Shows:
- A header "Site Inspector" with a sync status indicator (colored dot: green=online+synced, yellow=syncing, red=offline or pending)
- Quick action buttons: "New Inspection" and "Manage Sites"
- "Recent Inspections" list showing last 10 inspections with site name, date, status badge, and sync state icon
- Pending sync count badge

Mobile-first design - large touch targets (min 48px), cards layout.

```razor
@page "/"
@using SiteInspector.Client.Services
@using SiteInspector.Shared.Models
@inject IndexedDbService Db
@inject NavigationManager Nav
@inject SyncService Sync

<div class="page-header">
    <h1>🏗️ Site Inspector</h1>
    <div class="sync-indicator @GetSyncClass()" @onclick="SyncNow">
